<font face=helvetica size=3><b>Monday October 11, 1999</b></font>
			<hr align=LEFT size=1 width=500 color=#000080>
<!---------------news---------------->
<Br>
<font face=helvetica size=2 color=#000080><b>Irrational Games Hiring</b> - 19:33:21</font>
<br><br><blockquote>
Saw over at <a href=http://www.bluesnews.com>Blues</a> that <a href=http://www.irrational-games.com/>Irrational Games</a> makers of Theif and System Shock2 are hiring 3D Artists, Level Designers, and Programmers. Heres what they say about the level design position. <br><br><b>Level Designers<br> 
These positions are for level designers that have experience in building levels in current 3D engines in a current 3D game engine (Q2, Half-Life, Thief, Unreal etc.). They need to have playable examples of their work (single player levels are preferred). The better the level, the better the chances of being hired (IE sending work in progress or a level you just made in one night is not the best idea).</b><br><br> 
Read the full jobs page <a href=http://www.irrational-games.com/jobs.htm>here</a>.

<b><p align=right>Update by <a href="mailto:raygunn@gamedesign.net">raYGunn</a></p></b>
</blockquote>
<h3>Go <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net">back</a> to the main news page...</h3>
			</font>
